role.description: Role of the asset in relation to creative. Applicable to all but the following creative types: all REDIRECT and TRACKING_TEXT. This is a required field. PRIMARY applies to DISPLAY, FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER, IMAGE, DISPLAY_IMAGE_GALLERY, all RICH_MEDIA (which may contain multiple primary assets), and all VPAID creatives. BACKUP_IMAGE applies to FLASH_INPAGE, HTML5_BANNER, all RICH_MEDIA, and all VPAID creatives. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE. ADDITIONAL_IMAGE and ADDITIONAL_FLASH apply to FLASH_INPAGE creatives. OTHER refers to assets from sources other than Campaign Manager, such as Studio uploaded assets, applicable to all RICH_MEDIA and all VPAID creatives. PARENT_VIDEO refers to videos uploaded by the user in Campaign Manager and is applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO and VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives. TRANSCODED_VIDEO refers to videos transcoded by Campaign Manager from PARENT_VIDEO assets and is applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO and VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives. ALTERNATE_VIDEO refers to the Campaign Manager representation of child asset videos from Studio, and is applicable to VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives. These cannot be added or removed within Campaign Manager. For VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creatives, PARENT_VIDEO, TRANSCODED_VIDEO and ALTERNATE_VIDEO assets that are marked active serve as backup in case the VPAID creative cannot be served. Only PARENT_VIDEO assets can be added or removed for an INSTREAM_VIDEO or VPAID_LINEAR_VIDEO creative. PARENT_AUDIO refers to audios uploaded by the user in Campaign Manager and is applicable to INSTREAM_AUDIO creatives. TRANSCODED_AUDIO refers to audios transcoded by Campaign Manager from PARENT_AUDIO assets and is applicable to INSTREAM_AUDIO creatives.

collapsedSize.description: Size of an asset when collapsed. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA and all VPAID. Additionally, applicable to assets whose displayType is ASSET_DISPLAY_TYPE_EXPANDING or ASSET_DISPLAY_TYPE_PEEL_DOWN.

positionLeftUnit.description: Offset left unit for an asset. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

positionTopUnit.description: Offset top unit for an asset. This is a read-only field if the asset displayType is ASSET_DISPLAY_TYPE_OVERLAY. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

assetIdentifier.description: Identifier of this asset. This is the same identifier returned during creative asset insert operation. This is a required field. Applicable to all but the following creative types: all REDIRECT and TRACKING_TEXT.

companionCreativeIds.description: List of companion creatives assigned to an in-stream video creative asset. Acceptable values include IDs of existing flash and image creatives. Applicable to INSTREAM_VIDEO creative type with dynamicAssetSelection set to true.

windowMode.description: Window mode options for flash assets. Applicable to the following creative types: FLASH_INPAGE, RICH_MEDIA_DISPLAY_EXPANDING, RICH_MEDIA_IM_EXPAND, RICH_MEDIA_DISPLAY_BANNER, and RICH_MEDIA_INPAGE_FLOATING.

actionScript3.description: Whether ActionScript3 is enabled for the flash asset. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative type: FLASH_INPAGE. Applicable to DISPLAY when the primary asset type is not HTML_IMAGE.

position.description: Offset position for an asset. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

mediaDuration.description: Detected duration for audio or video asset. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: INSTREAM_AUDIO, INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

hideSelectionBoxes.description: Whether to hide selection boxes flag for an asset. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA.

audioSampleRate.description: Audio sample bit rate in hertz. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: INSTREAM_AUDIO, INSTREAM_VIDEO and all VPAID.

TargetableRemarketingList.description: Contains properties of a targetable remarketing list. Remarketing enables you to create lists of users who have performed specific actions on a site, then target ads to members of those lists. This resource is a read-only view of a remarketing list to be used to faciliate targeting ads to specific lists. Remarketing lists that are owned by your advertisers and those that are shared to your advertisers or account are accessible via this resource. To manage remarketing lists that are owned by your advertisers, use the RemarketingLists resource.

listSize.description: Number of users currently in the list. This is a read-only field.

name.description: Name of the targetable remarketing list. Is no greater than 128 characters long.

subaccountId.description: Subaccount ID of this remarketing list. This is a read-only, auto-generated field that is only returned in GET requests.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#targetableRemarketingList".

listSource.description: Product from which this targetable remarketing list was originated.

advertiserId.description: Dimension value for the advertiser ID that owns this targetable remarketing list.

lifeSpan.description: Number of days that a user should remain in the targetable remarketing list without an impression.

accountId.description: Account ID of this remarketing list. This is a read-only, auto-generated field that is only returned in GET requests.

advertiserIdDimensionValue.description: Dimension value for the ID of the advertiser.

active.description: Whether this targetable remarketing list is active.

CreativeGroup.description: Contains properties of a creative group.

advertiserIdDimensionValue.description: Dimension value for the ID of the advertiser. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

id.description: ID of this creative group. This is a read-only, auto-generated field.

advertiserId.description: Advertiser ID of this creative group. This is a required field on insertion.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#creativeGroup".

groupNumber.description: Subgroup of the creative group. Assign your creative groups to a subgroup in order to filter or manage them more easily. This field is required on insertion and is read-only after insertion. Acceptable values are 1 to 2, inclusive.

accountId.description: Account ID of this creative group. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

name.description: Name of this creative group. This is a required field and must be less than 256 characters long and unique among creative groups of the same advertiser.

subaccountId.description: Subaccount ID of this creative group. This is a read-only field that can be left blank.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#campaignsListResponse".

nextPageToken.description: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

rateOrCost.description: Rate or cost of this flight.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#languagesListResponse".

UserRolePermission.description: Contains properties of a user role permission.

id.description: ID of this user role permission.

availability.description: Levels of availability for a user role permission.

name.description: Name of this user role permission.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#userRolePermission".

permissionGroupId.description: ID of the permission group that this user role permission belongs to.

CompatibleFields.description: Represents a response to the queryCompatibleFields method.

pathAttributionReportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "PATH_ATTRIBUTION".

pathToConversionReportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "PATH_TO_CONVERSION".

floodlightReportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "FLOODLIGHT".

crossDimensionReachReportCompatibleField.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "CROSS_DIMENSION_REACH".

kind.description: The kind of resource this is, in this case dfareporting#compatibleFields.

reportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "STANDARD".

reachReportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "REACH".

pathReportCompatibleFields.description: Contains items that are compatible to be selected for a report of type "PATH".

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#siteVideoSettings".

skippableSettings.description: Settings for the skippability of video creatives served to this site. This will act as default for new placements created under this site.

companionSettings.description: Settings for the companion creatives of video creatives served to this site.

obaSettings.description: Settings for the OBA icon of video creatives served to this site. This will act as default for new placements created under this site.

transcodeSettings.description: Settings for the transcodes of video creatives served to this site. This will act as default for new placements created under this site.

obaEnabled.description: Whether OBA icons are enabled for this placement.

orientation.description: Orientation of a site template used for video. This will act as default for new placements created under this site.

enabled.description: Whether this campaign has enabled ad blocking. When true, ad blocking is enabled for placements in the campaign, but this may be overridden by site and placement settings. When false, ad blocking is disabled for all placements under the campaign, regardless of site and placement settings.

creativeBundleId.description: ID of a creative bundle to use for this campaign. If set, brand-neutral ads will select creatives from this bundle. Otherwise, a default transparent pixel will be used.

clickThroughUrl.description: Click-through URL used by brand-neutral ads. This is a required field when overrideClickThroughUrl is set to true.

overrideClickThroughUrl.description: Whether the brand-neutral ad's click-through URL comes from the campaign's creative bundle or the override URL. Must be set to true if ad blocking is enabled and no creative bundle is configured.

showAddressBar.description: Whether to display the browser address bar.

showMenuBar.description: Whether to display the browser menu bar.

showStatusBar.description: Whether to display the browser status bar.

showToolBar.description: Whether to display the browser tool bar.

offset.description: Upper-left corner coordinates of the popup window. Applicable if positionType is COORDINATES.

positionType.description: Popup window position either centered or at specific coordinate.

dimension.description: Popup dimension for a creative. This is a read-only field. Applicable to the following creative types: all RICH_MEDIA and all VPAID

showScrollBar.description: Whether to display the browser scroll bar.

targetWindowOption.description: Type of browser window for which the backup image of the flash creative can be displayed.

impressions.description: Number of times an individual user can be served the ad within the specified duration. Acceptable values are 1 to 15, inclusive.

duration.description: Duration of time, in seconds, for this frequency cap. The maximum duration is 90 days. Acceptable values are 1 to 7776000, inclusive.

nextPageToken.description: Pagination token to be used for the next list operation.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dfareporting#remarketingListsListResponse".
